## Privacy Policy 

This is the Privacy Policy for [{{name}}]({{include.url}}) (“the Software") which is owned and licensed by [{{licensor}}]({{site.url}}) (“the Licensor").

We are committed to your privacy and in being transparent regarding our data collection practices. This privacy policy explains how the Software handles data when integrated into other products.


## In short

- The Software does not collect any personal data.
- The Software may collect anonymous usage statistics and crash reports.
- All collected data is intended to improve Software functionality and reliability.


## Definitions

**Personal Data**: Information that can be used to identify you as an individual, either directly (such as your name or email) or indirectly (through combinations of data points).

**Anonymous Data**: Information that can't be used to identify you as an individual and that has been aggregated or anonymized to remove any identifying characteristics.


## Data Collection

### What We Don't Collect

The Software does not collect:

- Personal identifiers (names, email addresses, phone numbers)
- Device identifiers that could be used for tracking
- Any data that could identify individual users
- User-generated content
- Location data


### What We May Collect

The Software may collect anonymous data including:

- **Usage Statistics**: How frequently the Software and it's features are used, to understand feature adoption.
- **Crash Reports**: Technical information about Software failures, including error messages and stack traces.
- **Performance Metrics**: Performance and resource usage, to understand & improve Software performance.


## Data Storage

The Software may store anonymous, aggregated data:

- Within the Software until it's synced to cloud-storage.
- Securely on servers with industry-standard encryption.
- Only as long as necessary for the purposes described in this policy.


## Data Sharing

The Software may share anonymous, aggregated data with:

- **Our Development Team**: To improve Software functionality and fix issues.
- **Analytics Services**: Third-party services that help us analyze usage patterns.

{{licensor}} does not:

- Sell data to third parties
- Share data with advertisers
- Provide data to any party for marketing purposes


## Your Rights

